{
  "texts": [
    "Among them, event detection aims to identify specific types of event trigger words from a given text; it is a key step in event extraction [40].",
    "Event Element Extraction identifies the elements of a particular event and marks its role [41].",
    "For example, in the sentence \"Biden swears inauguration at Capitol on January 20\", the event extraction task is specifically to detect the trigger word \"inauguration\", which is the incident type; The words \"Biden\", \"January 20\" and \"Capitol\" are as the event elements, which can be determined as \"person\", \"time\" and \"place\", respectively.The implementation of the above event extraction task is based on the technical basis of word segmentation, part-ofspeech, and propositional entity recognition [42,43].",
    "The extracted structured information can further support deeper mining and understanding of unstructured text.Table IV summarizes the main methods for event extraction.",
    "The methods can be classified into pattern-matching-based methods and machine learning-based methods."
  ]
}